Again
---------------------------------------
cd simple
vi hello2.cpp
g++ hello2.cpp
./a.out
git status
git add *
git commit -m "second program"
git push origin main

to update to latest changes
git pull

branching
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
now created a new branch here for data structures
git branch ds
git checkout ds
(you can combine both above commands with "git branch -b ds") --- -c i guess
( new way - git switch -c ds to create & switch, git switch main, git switch ds to switch, but if you already have a 2 brnaches and when u clone, it wont checkout locally,
So you have to chekout it locally, -- GOTO -- ****checkout_after_long*****)
once you are in that branch you can do things
mkdir data-structures
cd data-structures
touch array.cpp
git status
git add dta-structures
git push origin ds

branch merging (future)
--------------------------------
git checkout main
git merge ds (solve if any conflicts)
git status
git branch -d ds ( to delete the branch)

checkout_after_long: --- checkout repo with multiple branches
-----------------------------------------------------------------
git clone git@github.com:RoshanAnthon/C.git

pereirar@JNPR-MAC-P9W463 C % git branch
* main
pereirar@JNPR-MAC-P9W463 C % git branch -a
* main
  remotes/origin/HEAD -> origin/main
  remotes/origin/ds
  remotes/origin/main

pereirar@JNPR-MAC-P9W463 C % git checkout -b ds origin/ds
pereirar@JNPR-MAC-P9W463 C % ls  (magic!!- you only see ds files)
pereirar@JNPR-MAC-P9W463 C % git branch
* ds
  main
pereirar@JNPR-MAC-P9W463 C % git switch main
Switched to branch 'main'
Your branch is up to date with 'origin/main'.
pereirar@JNPR-MAC-P9W463 C % git branch     
  ds
* main
pereirar@JNPR-MAC-P9W463 C % ls (magic!!- you see a lot of files)






